HOUSE BILL 929
L2, Q2 6lr1555
HB 851/25 – ENT & W&M CF SB 450
By: Carroll County Delegation
Introduced and read first time: February 5, 2026
Assigned to: Economic Matters and Ways and Means
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Carroll County – Office of Permits and Inspections – Denial of Commercial
3 Permit or License for Unpaid Personal Property Taxes
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the Carroll County Office of Permits and Inspections from
5 issuing or renewing a commercial license or permit in the county if the applicant has
6 unpaid personal property taxes except under certain circumstances; authorizing the
7 Carroll County Office of Permits and Inspections to issue or renew a commercial
8 license or permit if the applicant submits certain evidence that the applicant has
9 paid any previously unpaid personal property taxes; and generally relating to the
10 issuance or renewal of commercial licenses and permits in Carroll County.
11 BY adding to
12 Article – Local Government
13 Section 12–906
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2013 Volume and 2025 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Local Government
19 12–906.
20 (A) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY TO CARROLL COUNTY.
21 (B) (1) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW AND SUBJECT
22 TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, THE CARROLL COUNTY OFFICE OF
23 PERMITS AND INSPECTIONS MAY DENY THE ISSUANCE OR RENEWAL OF A
24 COMMERCIAL LICENSE OR PERMIT IN THE COUNTY IF THE APPLICANT HAS UNPAID
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb0929*

2 HOUSE BILL 929
1 PERSONAL PROPERTY TAXES.
2 (2) THE CARROLL COUNTY OFFICE OF PERMITS AND INSPECTIONS
3 MAY NOT DENY THE ISSUANCE OR RENEWAL OF A COMMERCIAL LICENSE OR PERMIT
4 FOR UNPAID PERSONAL PROPERTY TAXES UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
5 SUBSECTION IF THE APPLICANT SUBMITS EVIDENCE TO THE SATISFACTION OF THE
6 OFFICE THAT THE APPLICANT HAS DISPUTED THE AMOUNT OF UNPAID PERSONAL
7 PROPERTY TAXES.
8 (C) THE CARROLL COUNTY OFFICE OF PERMITS AND INSPECTIONS MAY
9 ISSUE OR RENEW A COMMERCIAL LICENSE OR PERMIT IN THE COUNTY THAT WAS
10 DENIED UNDER SUBSECTION (B)(1) OF THIS SECTION IF THE APPLICANT SUBMITS
11 EVIDENCE TO THE SATISFACTION OF THE OFFICE THAT THE APPLICANT HAS PAID
12 ANY PREVIOUSLY UNPAID PERSONAL PROPERTY TAXES.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
14 October 1, 2026.

